CROSSFIRE Registry — License

This repository contains cryptographic hash values (SHA-256, SHA-512) and
digital signatures for publicly distributed software binaries.

Hash values are mathematical facts derived from publicly available files.
Their publication for security research and defensive purposes is protected
under applicable law in most jurisdictions.

USE:
  - Permitted: defensive security tooling, research, education, journalism
  - Permitted: verifying download integrity of software you are entitled to use
  - Not permitted: circumventing software licensing or access controls
  - Not permitted: any offensive use

THE REGISTRY IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND.
The authors make no guarantee of completeness or currency of hash values.
Always verify critical software through multiple independent channels.

